hopobject.body: Best Site good looking fishbase.org Many people say they want to stay on the job simply because they like working (41 percent). A job often offers mental stimulation and a way to stay active (51 percent) in retirement. And a few people (19 percent) no longer need the income from a job, but stick around for other aspects of the workplace they enjoy. "Most people who have participated in the workplace over the last 30 years have found themselves in a position of importance or relevance, and it's very hard to walk away from being relevant," says Brian Schwartz, a vice president and financial advisor for HSBC Securities.
